<subSubSection id="6EB532DEFFE1FF85FF1095FAFDB0FB93" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="description">
<paragraph id="26106155FFE1FF85FF1095FAFDB0FB93" blockId="25.[163,779,663,1083]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<taxonomicName id="E1AF1AD6FFE1FF85FF1095FAFDBBFD04" box="[163,533,663,684]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Pseudoanthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="karakalense">
<emphasis id="14DBBD47FFE1FF85FF1095FAFDBBFD04" box="[163,533,663,684]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Pseudoanthidium karakalense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from Kara-Kala in 
<collectingCountry id="5EB821C5FFE1FF85FED295DBFDB2FD63" box="[353,540,693,715]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
. Popov described 
<taxonomicName id="E1AF1AD6FFE1FF85FF1095B8FEE4FD41" box="[163,330,724,746]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Pseudoanthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="karakalense">
<emphasis id="14DBBD47FFE1FF85FF1095B8FEE4FD41" box="[163,330,724,746]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">P. karakalense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as similar to 
<taxonomicName id="E1AF1AD6FFE1FF85FE5D95B8FDDFFD41" authorityName="Dusmet y Alsonso" authorityYear="1915" box="[494,625,724,746]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Anthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="astilleroi">
<emphasis id="14DBBD47FFE1FF85FE5D95B8FDDFFD41" box="[494,625,724,746]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">P. astilleroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but with the female differing in certain morphological characters, including the punctation on the frons, the straight edge of the clypeal margin, the length of the first, second and third antennal segments and the paler yellow colour. He further noted that this taxon differed from 
<taxonomicName id="E1AF1AD6FFE1FF85FF5094E0FEDBFC09" box="[227,373,908,930]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Zygophyllaceae" genus="Pseuodanthidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygophyllales" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lituratum">
<emphasis id="14DBBD47FFE1FF85FF5094E0FEDBFC09" box="[227,373,908,930]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">P. lituratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its punctation, size, coloration and male genitalia. A careful examination of Popov’s 
<typeStatus id="F914DFF7FFE1FF85FF1094A7FF78FC77" box="[163,214,970,991]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">type</typeStatus>
material confirms the synonymy of this taxon with 
<taxonomicName id="E1AF1AD6FFE1FF85FF509484FE0BFC56" baseAuthorityName="Dours" baseAuthorityYear="1873" box="[227,421,1001,1022]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Pseudoanthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stigmaticorne">
<emphasis id="14DBBD47FFE1FF85FF509484FE0BFC56" box="[227,421,1001,1022]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">P. stigmaticorne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="423E1CA4FFE1FF85FE069485FDDDFC56" author="Warncke K" box="[437,627,1000,1022]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="119 - 210" refId="ref36293" refString="Warncke K. 1980. Die Bienengattung Anthidium Fabricius, 1804 in der Westpalaarktis und im turkestanischen Becken. Entomofauna 1: 119 - 210." type="journal article" year="1980">Warncke (1980)</bibRefCitation>
erroneously placed this taxon in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName id="E1AF1AD6FFE1FF85FDFC936AFD4FFBB4" box="[591,737,1031,1052]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Pseudoanthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cribratum">
<emphasis id="14DBBD47FFE1FF85FDFC936AFD4FFBB4" box="[591,737,1031,1052]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">P. cribratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName id="E1AF1AD6FFE1FF85FF109348FDA1FB92" authorityName="Morawitz" authorityYear="1875" box="[163,527,1061,1082]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Anthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="lituratum" subSpecies="cribratum">
<emphasis id="14DBBD47FFE1FF85FF109348FDA1FB92" box="[163,527,1061,1082]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Anthidium lituratum cribratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6EB532DEFFE1FF85FF109308FB4AFD4C" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="26106155FFE1FF85FF109308FD89F98F" blockId="25.[163,779,1124,1575]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="14DBBD47FFE1FF85FF109308FEC2FBD1" box="[163,364,1124,1146]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Diagnosis female:</emphasis>
The female of 
<taxonomicName id="E1AF1AD6FFE1FF85FDAC9308FD7DFBD2" baseAuthorityName="Dours" baseAuthorityYear="1873" box="[543,723,1125,1146]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Pseudoanthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stigmaticorne">
<emphasis id="14DBBD47FFE1FF85FDAC9308FD7DFBD2" box="[543,723,1125,1146]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">P. stigmaticorne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be distinguished from other members of this complex by the following combination of characters: punctation on terga comparatively coarse, as large or larger than punctation on mesonotum and with shiny interspaces between punctures; largest punctures on black part of scutellum smaller in diameter than largest punctures on T2; punctation on vertex between lateral ocellus, eye and postoccipital margin small but distinct, with shiny narrow spaces between most punctures; clypeus either yellow, yellow with black markings or black; small, mostly less than 
<quantity id="E157CCB0FFE1FF85FE7692D8FDB1FA63" box="[453,543,1461,1483]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="mm" value="0.8">0.8 mm</quantity>
(
<figureCitation id="BE947DD0FFE1FF85FD8292D8FD76FA63" box="[561,728,1461,1483]" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="23.[164,244,1201,1223]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,195,1161]" captionTargetId="figure-344@23.[323,1283,195,1161]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Figure 17. Dorsal habitus, females. A, vertex Pseudoanthidium stigmaticorne (Arzens, France); B, vertex P. cribratum (Bukhara, Uzbekistan); C, mesonotum P.stigmaticorne (Arzens, France); D, mesonotum P.cribratum (Bukhara, Uzbekistan); E, metasoma P. stigmaticorne (Arzens, France); F, metasoma P. cribratum (Bukhara, Uzbekistan)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5817312" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5817312/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 17A, C, E</figureCitation>
). In their zone of overlap (e.g. in 
<collectingRegion id="E46BAFB7FFE1FF85FE4092B9FDE2FA42" box="[499,588,1492,1514]" country="Ukraine" name="Crimea" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Crimea</collectingRegion>
), differentiating females of 
<taxonomicName id="E1AF1AD6FFE1FF85FE91929EFE73F9A0" baseAuthorityName="Dours" baseAuthorityYear="1873" box="[290,477,1523,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Pseudoanthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stigmaticorne">
<emphasis id="14DBBD47FFE1FF85FE91929EFE73F9A0" box="[290,477,1523,1544]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">P. stigmaticorne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from those of 
<taxonomicName id="E1AF1AD6FFE1FF85FD3A929EFCA5F9AF" authorityName="Mocsary" authorityYear="1879" box="[649,779,1522,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Anthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenellum">
<emphasis id="14DBBD47FFE1FF85FD3A929EFCA5F9AF" box="[649,779,1522,1544]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">P. tenellum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be challenging in some cases.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="26106155FFE1FF85FF10913DFB4AFD4C" blockId="25.[163,779,1616,1883]" lastBlockId="25.[827,1444,197,740]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="14DBBD47FFE1FF85FF10913DFEF5F9CD" box="[163,347,1616,1637]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Diagnosis male:</emphasis>
The male of 
<taxonomicName id="E1AF1AD6FFE1FF85FE4B913CFD1EF9CD" baseAuthorityName="Dours" baseAuthorityYear="1873" box="[504,688,1616,1638]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Pseudoanthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stigmaticorne">
<emphasis id="14DBBD47FFE1FF85FE4B913CFD1EF9CD" box="[504,688,1616,1638]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">P. stigmaticorne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be distinguished from other members of this complex by the following combination of characters: gonostylus approximately 1.5 times wider at widest point than at base (
<figureCitation id="BE947DD0FFE1FF85FEB891A7FE20F948" box="[267,398,1738,1760]" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="24.[145,224,1340,1362]" captionTargetBox="[225,1345,195,1301]" captionTargetId="figure-257@24.[225,1345,195,1301]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figure 18. Gonostyli, Pseudoanthidium stigmaticorne. A, Cape Lukull, Crimea; B, Bet She’an, Israel; C, Agadir, Morocco; D, Restinclières, France; E, Cacela Velha, Portugal; F, Seui, Sardinia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5817314" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5817314/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 18A–F</figureCitation>
); exterior margin of gonostylus relatively straight, inner margin more sharply rounded toward apex (
<figureCitation id="BE947DD0FFE1FF85FE8C9065FE13F8B5" box="[319,445,1800,1822]" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="24.[145,224,1340,1362]" captionTargetBox="[225,1345,195,1301]" captionTargetId="figure-257@24.[225,1345,195,1301]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figure 18. Gonostyli, Pseudoanthidium stigmaticorne. A, Cape Lukull, Crimea; B, Bet She’an, Israel; C, Agadir, Morocco; D, Restinclières, France; E, Cacela Velha, Portugal; F, Seui, Sardinia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5817314" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5817314/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 18A–F</figureCitation>
); notch at apex of gonostylus either as deep as opening of notch is wide and more or less centred at apex of gonostylus (most European and Central Asian populations) or notch significantly less deep than opening of notch is wide and strongly offset laterally (northern Africa, southern 
<collectingCountry id="5EB821C5FFE1FF85FAA4966FFAE0FEB0" box="[1303,1358,258,280]" name="Italy" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Italy</collectingCountry>
) (notch deeper in other species) (
<figureCitation id="BE947DD0FFE1FF85FBEF964CFB74FE9E" box="[1116,1242,289,311]" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="24.[145,224,1340,1362]" captionTargetBox="[225,1345,195,1301]" captionTargetId="figure-257@24.[225,1345,195,1301]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figure 18. Gonostyli, Pseudoanthidium stigmaticorne. A, Cape Lukull, Crimea; B, Bet She’an, Israel; C, Agadir, Morocco; D, Restinclières, France; E, Cacela Velha, Portugal; F, Seui, Sardinia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5817314" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5817314/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 18A–F</figureCitation>
); lateral comb on S5 small, with longest teeth shorter than maximal width of hind basitarsus (comb larger in 
<taxonomicName id="E1AF1AD6FFE1FF85FAA09632FA33FEDB" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1809" box="[1299,1437,350,372]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Anthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scapulare">
<emphasis id="14DBBD47FFE1FF85FAA09632FA33FEDB" box="[1299,1437,350,372]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">P. scapulare</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E1AF1AD6FFE1FF85FC889613FC06FE3B" box="[827,936,382,403]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Pseudoanthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nanum">
