); darkened raised zone across S2 with only short, sparse hairs, in shape of ‘moustache’ (
<figureCitation id="BE947DD0FFE1FF85FB0E95FCFA8DFD0E" box="[1213,1315,657,679]" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="19.[163,244,1498,1520]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,195,1458]" captionTargetId="figure-171@19.[323,1283,195,1458]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 13. S2, males. A, Pseudoanthidium nanum (Dordogne, France); B, P. scapulare (Argèles-sur-Mer, France); C, P. stigmaticorne (Cabanes de Fleury, France); D, P. tenellum (Krasnoperekopsk, Crimea); E, P. palestinicum (Jerusalem, Israel); F, P. cribratum (Ayelet Hashar, Israel); G, P. kaspareki (Side, Turkey); H, P. rozeni (Hanna, Pakistan)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5817304" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5817304/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 13C</figureCitation>
